      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, of course it could and it would make code *this* simpler.\nBut not the call sites, which would require more boilerplate.\n\nWhat I really want is Py equivalent of:\n\n  def vote(label, value, time\u003dNone, user\u003dNone):\n    assert (time is None) \u003d\u003d (user is None)\n\ns.t. usage is concise and easy to read:\ngf.CQ(+2)\ngf.CQ(+2, epoch.Add(time.Minute), gf.U(\"user-1\"))\n\nMy ideal is avoiding the need for `gf.U()` by passing just \"user-1\", but I guess I can tolerate gf.U for now.",
